***An important message from Chesapeake Schools***

Due to Governor Dewine lifting restrictions on sports the Chesapeake School System has re-instated sports for this year with restrictions. All athletes, coaches, cheerleaders, and band members will be required to sign a waiver holding the district harmless in the case of illness. Also, each participant will be allowed 2 spectators who will be required to sign a waiver upon entrance. We are happy the governor rescinded these concerns so our kids can participate in fall sports.

Today is national Teacher appreciation day! Today we say thank you to our teachers. We applaud you for doing the impossible. We are unified in saying that there isn't any replacement for what you do.

post_text:
Ohio Governor Mike Dewine announced today that all K-12 Ohio schools will be closed through the remainder of the 2019 - 2020 school year due to the COVID-19 pandemic.

Also, Completed educational packet dropoff will take place on Friday, May 1st at your student's school. The hours for dropoff are 7 AM to 8:30 AM and 5:30 PM to 7 PM. Please make certain your child's name and grade level are printed on the outside of each packet.

You will also be given the last educational packet to be completed for this school year.

Thank you and be safe.

post_text:
Grab and Go Bags

Chesapeake School District Student Breakfast and Lunch Program

Beginning Monday, March 23rd, 2020 Chesapeake Schools will make Grab and Go food bags available to our students at three locations in our school district.

Grab and Go bags will be delivered to three separate locations for those unable to pick up food at Chesapeake Elementary.

Chesapeake Community Center
Collins Career and Technical Center
Big Branch Church

The Grab and Go bags will be available at 12:30 PM in each location.

Food pick up will continue to be available at Chesapeake Elementary between 11:30 AM and 1:00 PM if you do not use the delivery service.

If you plan to pick up bags at one of these locations please call the Chesapeake Board of Education Office between the hours of 9:00 AM and 1:00 PM on Thursday, March 19th or Friday, March 20th.

We are very proud and appreciative of everyone that has made Grab and Go food bags possible.

post_text:
An NTID or Non-Traditional Instruction Day allows Chesapeake Union Exempted Village School District to provide non-traditional instruction to students on days when Students are unable to attend due to a district wide closing. On the designated NTI Days, students will have assignments (either online or paper packets) that provide continuation of learning, review, and standardized core focus. Depending on the student’s grade level, the assignments may contain lessons from reading/language arts, mathematics, social studies, and writing along with other curricular lessons. Lessons are supported with online resources but can be completed without access to the Internet.

Follow the link below to view, download, and/or print any NTID packets you may need.

https://www.peake.k12.oh.us/NTID.aspx

David Ridenour‎Chesapeake,Ohio School Transportation
February 13 at 1:45 PM ·

Bus Changes due to high water.

Bus #6 - Water over at Chesapeake High School.

Bus #8 - Water over Indian Guyan. Pick up at the fabrication shop.

Bus #9 - Water over at CR 104. Parents may pick their children up on McIntyre Road intersection or Brentwood bridge..

Bus #12 - Water over Dogtown. - Parents may pick their children up at Monty's pizza or the Community Center.

Bus #15 - Water over at Plumley Poynter. Students may ride Bus #10 to Heatherbrooke at Roger's garage or meet Bus #15 at Macri's Market.

Also, remember the water is over at Chesapeake High School. If you are picking up a child please pull into a parking space. DO NOT BLOCK the travel lane when you are picking up unless the lane is clear. With water over the road we can not have extra traffic out on County Road 1 without a sever traffic problem..

post_text:
After School Students

The Chesapeake High School After School Program will be hosting a Life Skills Event Thursday from 6 to 8PM. Parents are asked to join as students learn some basic fundamentals of money budgeting and investments, nutritional values, and interview techniques and resume' building. Food will also be donated by Smoke Em if you got em BBQ for all participants. Parents will also be shown how to access student's grades.

post_text:
The Southeast District Athletic Board has gone to all online sales for boys’ and girls’ basketball presale tickets at the sectional and district tournaments. The Board reduced the price of the presale ticket by $1.00 to help offset the fees associated with online ticket purchasing. Tickets purchased at the gate will remain $5.00 for sectional and $6.00 for district tournament games.

The link to purchase online tickets is
https://ohsaa.org/tickets.

Purchasers may choose the game they wish to attend and designate their support. Upon the conclusion of the game, the purchasers of tickets for the winning team will automatically receive an email with details to purchase tickets for the next game.
